    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-Mussel Oligopeptide-1 is a single chain recombinant protein produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized to be identical to the gene which codes for Polyphenolic Phosphoprotein MEFP-5 found in the mussel, Mytilus edulis. Polyphenolic Phosphoprotein MEFP-5 contains a maximum of 1245 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
